{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884171114,"sessionID":"ses_2850e5115ffehvvEY1tK0F0KI3","part":{"id":"prt_d7af1f335001ltOCj6cHMiNEUi","messageID":"msg_d7af1de4e001aUsJ3wNnm0ww6v","sessionID":"ses_2850e5115ffehvvEY1tK0F0KI3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0d6c724ca7594ec58aabc1d64c92d37b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Define the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                         Helm Chart Structure                                 │\n24: │                     manifests/charts/base/                                   │\n25: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n26: │                                                                              │\n27: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐      │\n28: │  │   Chart.yaml     │    │   values.yaml    │    │  templates/_*    │      │\n29: │  │  (Metadata)      │───▶│  (Config)        │───▶│  (Rendered YAML) │      │\n30: │  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘      │\n31: │                                                                              │\n32: │  Templates:                                                                  │\n33: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n34: │  │ workloadmanager.yaml        │ Deployment + Service                   │    │\n35: │  │ agentcube-router.yaml       │ Deployment + Service                   │    │\n36: │  │ rbac/workloadmanager.yaml   │ SA, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding   │    │\n37: │  │ rbac-router.yaml            │ SA, Role, RoleBinding (conditional)   │    │\n38: │  │ volcano-agent-scheduler     │ Scheduler resources (conditional)      │    │\n39: │  │ _helpers.tpl                │ Named template helpers                 │    │\n40: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n41: │                                                                              │\n42: │  CRDs (crds/):                                                               │\n43: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n44: │  │ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml                      │    │\n45: │  │ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml                   │    │\n46: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n47: │                                                                              │\n48: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Deployment Model\n52: \n53: ```\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                                       │\n56: │                      Namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}                     │\n57: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n58: │                                                                              │\n59: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n60: │  │                    AgentCube Components                                 │ │\n61: │  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │\n62: │  │                                                                         │ │\n63: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐         ┌───────────────────┐                  │ │\n64: │  │  │ workloadmanager   │         │ agentcube-router  │                  │ │\n65: │  │  │ Deployment        │◀───────▶│ Deployment        │                  │ │\n66: │  │  │ (replicas: 1)     │         │ (replicas: 1)     │                  │ │\n67: │  │  │ Port: 8080        │         │ Port: 8080        │                  │ │\n68: │  │  └───────────────────┘         └───────────────────┘                  │ │\n69: │  │          │                              │                              │ │\n70: │  │          │                              │                              │ │\n71: │  │          ▼                              ▼                              │ │\n72: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐         ┌───────────────────┐                  │ │\n73: │  │  │ workloadmanager   │         │ agentcube-router  │                  │ │\n74: │  │  │ Service (ClusterIP│         │ Service (ClusterIP│                  │ │\n75: │  │  │  port: 8080)      │         │  port: 8080)      │                  │ │\n76: │  │  └───────────────────┘         └───────────────────┘                  │ │\n77: │  │                                                                         │ │\n78: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐                                                │ │\n79: │  │  │ redis Deployment  │    (if enabled, external or bundled)          │ │\n80: │  │  │ redis Service     │                                                │ │\n81: │  │  │ Port: 6379        │                                                │ │\n82: │  │  └───────────────────┘                                                │ │\n83: │  │                                                                         │ │\n84: │  │  ┌───────────────────┐                                                │ │\n85: │  │  │ volcano-agent-    │    (if volcano.scheduler.enabled)             │ │\n86: │  │  │ scheduler         │                                                │ │\n87: │  │  └───────────────────┘                                                │ │\n88: │  │                                                                         │ │\n89: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n90: │                                                                              │\n91: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n92: │  │                    RBAC Resources                                       │ │\n93: │  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │\n94: │  │  ServiceAccount: workloadmanager (cluster-scoped)                      │ │\n95: │  │  ServiceAccount: agentcube-router (namespace-scoped, conditional)      │ │\n96: │  │  ServiceAccount: volcano-agent-scheduler (cluster-scoped, conditional) │ │\n97: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n98: │                                                                              │\n99: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n100: │  │                    Secrets                                              │ │\n101: │  ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │\n102: │  │  jwt-secret: JWT signing key (optional)                                │ │\n103: │  │  identity-secret: Picod-Router identity (optional)                     │ │\n104: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n105: │                                                                              │\n106: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ### Component Relationships\n110: \n111: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n112: |-----------|------|--------------|\n113: | `Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion) | None |\n114: | `values.yaml` | Default configuration values | Chart.yaml (version reference) |\n115: | `_helpers.tpl` | Named template helpers (name, fullname, labels) | values.yaml |\n116: | `workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service | values.yaml, _helpers.tpl |\n117: | `agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment + Service | values.yaml, _helpers.tpl, workloadmanager Service |\n118: | `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | RBAC for WorkloadManager | _helpers.tpl, workloadmanager.yaml |\n119: | `rbac-router.yaml` | RBAC for Router (conditional) | _helpers.tpl, agentcube-router.yaml |\n120: | `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Volcano scheduler (conditional) | values.yaml, _helpers.tpl |\n121: | `crds/*.yaml` | CRD definitions (installed before templates) | controller-gen |\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## Data Structures\n126: \n127: ### Chart.yaml Schema\n128: \n129: ```yaml\n130: apiVersion: v1\n131: name: agentcube\n132: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n133: type: application\n134: version: 0.1.0        # Chart version (SemVer 2)\n135: appVersion: 1.0.0     # Application version\n136: keywords:\n137:   - agentcube\n138:   - kubernetes\n139:   - sandbox\n140:   - ai-agents\n141: maintainers:\n142:   - name: volcano-sh\n143:     email: volcano-sh@example.com\n144: sources:\n145:   - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n146: ```\n147: \n148: ### values.yaml Schema\n149: \n150: ```yaml\n151: # Global settings\n152: imagePullSecrets: []           # array[string] - Secret names for private registries\n153: nameOverride: \"\"               # string - Partial name override\n154: fullnameOverride: \"\"           # string - Full name override\n155: \n156: # Redis connection (must be provided by user)\n157: redis:\n158:   addr: \"\"                     # string - Redis address (host:port)\n159:   password: \"\"                 # string - Redis password (empty = no auth)\n160: \n161: # WorkloadManager configuration\n162: workloadmanager:\n163:   replicas: 1                  # int - Deployment replicas\n164:   image:\n165:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n166:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n167:     tag: latest\n168:   service:\n169:     type: ClusterIP\n170:     port: 8080\n171:   resources:\n172:     limits:\n173:       cpu: 500m\n174:       memory: 512Mi\n175:     requests:\n176:       cpu: 100m\n177:       memory: 128Mi\n178:   extraEnv: []                 # array[object] - Extra environment variables\n179: \n180: # Router configuration\n181: router:\n182:   replicas: 1\n183:   image:\n184:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n185:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n186:     tag: latest\n187:   service:\n188:     type: ClusterIP\n189:     port: 8080\n190:     targetPort: 8080\n191:   resources:\n192:     limits:\n193:       cpu: 500m\n194:       memory: 512Mi\n195:     requests:\n196:       cpu: 100m\n197:       memory: 128Mi\n198:   config: {}                   # object - Router configuration\n199:   extraEnv: []                 # array[object] - Extra environment variables\n200:   serviceAccountName: \"\"       # string - ServiceAccount name (empty = default)\n201:   rbac:\n202:     create: false              # bool - Create RBAC resources\n203: \n204: # Volcano scheduler (optional)\n205: volcano:\n206:   scheduler:\n207:     enabled: false             # bool - Enable Volcano agent scheduler\n208:     replicas: 1\n209:     image:\n210:       repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n211:       pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n212:       tag: latest\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ### Values Type Definitions\n216: \n217: | Path | Type | Default | Description |\n218: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n219: | `imagePullSecrets` | `array[string]` | `[]` | Secret names for private registries |\n220: | `nameOverride` | `string` | `\"\"` | Partial name override |\n221: | `fullnameOverride` | `string` | `\"\"` | Full name override |\n222: | `redis.addr` | `string` | `\"\"` | Redis address (`host:port`) |\n223: | `redis.password` | `string` | `\"\"` | Redis password |\n224: | `router.replicas` | `int` | `1` | Router deployment replicas |\n225: | `router.image.repository` | `string` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` | Router image repository |\n226: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | `string` | `IfNotPresent` | Image pull policy |\n227: | `router.image.tag` | `string` | `latest` | Router image tag |\n228: | `router.service.type` | `string` | `ClusterIP` | Router service type |\n229: | `router.service.port` | `int` | `8080` | Router service port |\n230: | `router.service.targetPort` | `int` | `8080` | Router container port |\n231: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | `string` | `500m` | CPU limit |\n232: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | `string` | `512Mi` | Memory limit |\n233: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | `string` | `100m` | CPU request |\n234: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | `string` | `128Mi` | Memory request |\n235: | `router.serviceAccountName` | `string` | `\"\"` | ServiceAccount name |\n236: | `router.rbac.create` | `bool` | `false` | Create Router RBAC |\n237: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | `int` | `1` | WorkloadManager replicas |\n238: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | `string` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` | WorkloadManager image |\n239: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | `int` | `8080` | WorkloadManager service port |\n240: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | `bool` | `false` | Enable Volcano scheduler |\n241: \n242: ### Named Templates (_helpers.tpl)\n243: \n244: ```yaml\n245: {{- define \"agentcube.name\" -}}\n246: {{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n247: {{- end -}}\n248: \n249: {{- define \"agentcube.fullname\" -}}\n250: {{- if .Values.fullnameOverride -}}\n251: {{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n252: {{- else -}}\n253: {{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride -}}\n254: {{- if contains $name .Release.Name -}}\n255: {{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n256: {{- else -}}\n257: {{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" -}}\n258: {{- end -}}\n259: {{- end -}}\n260: {{- end -}}\n261: \n262: {{- define \"agentcube.labels\" -}}\n263: app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n264: app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n265: app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}\n266: app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n267: {{- end -}}\n268: \n269: {{- define \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" -}}\n270: app: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n271: {{- end -}}\n272: \n273: {{- define \"agentcube.image\" -}}\n274: {{- $registry := .Values.global.imageRegistry | default \"\" -}}\n275: {{- $repository := .repository -}}\n276: {{- $tag := .tag | default \"latest\" -}}\n277: {{- if $registry -}}\n278: {{- printf \"%s/%s:%s\" $registry $repository $tag -}}\n279: {{- else -}}\n280: {{- printf \"%s:%s\" $repository $tag -}}\n281: {{- end -}}\n282: {{- end -}}\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## API Contracts\n288: \n289: ### WorkloadManager Deployment Template\n290: \n291: ```yaml\n292: apiVersion: apps/v1\n293: kind: Deployment\n294: metadata:\n295:   name: workloadmanager\n296:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n297:   labels:\n298:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n299: spec:\n300:   replicas: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}\n301:   selector:\n302:     matchLabels:\n303:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n304:       app: workloadmanager\n305:   template:\n306:     metadata:\n307:       labels:\n308:         {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n309:         app: workloadmanager\n310:     spec:\n311:       serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\n312:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n313:       imagePullSecrets:\n314:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n315:       {{- end }}\n316:       containers:\n317:         - name: workloadmanager\n318:           image: \"{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\"\n319:           imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}\n320:           ports:\n321:             - name: http\n322:               containerPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n323:               protocol: TCP\n324:           env:\n325:             - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n326:               valueFrom:\n327:                 fieldRef:\n328:                   fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n329:             - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n330:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.password }}\"\n331:             - name: REDIS_ADDR\n332:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.addr }}\"\n333:             {{- with .Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv }}\n334:             {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}\n335:             {{- end }}\n336:           args:\n337:             - --port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n338:             - --runtime-class-name=\n339:           resources:\n340:             {{- toYaml .Values.workloadmanager.resources | nindent 12 }}\n341:           livenessProbe:\n342:             httpGet:\n343:               path: /health\n344:               port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n345:             initialDelaySeconds: 10\n346:             periodSeconds: 10\n347:           readinessProbe:\n348:             httpGet:\n349:               path: /health\n350:               port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n351:             initialDelaySeconds: 5\n352:             periodSeconds: 5\n353: ```\n354: \n355: ### WorkloadManager Service Template\n356: \n357: ```yaml\n358: apiVersion: v1\n359: kind: Service\n360: metadata:\n361:   name: workloadmanager\n362:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n363:   labels:\n364:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n365: spec:\n366:   type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}\n367:   ports:\n368:     - port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n369:       targetPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n370:       protocol: TCP\n371:       name: http\n372:   selector:\n373:     app: workloadmanager\n374: ```\n375: \n376: ### Router Deployment Template\n377: \n378: ```yaml\n379: apiVersion: apps/v1\n380: kind: Deployment\n381: metadata:\n382:   name: agentcube-router\n383:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n384:   labels:\n385:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n386: spec:\n387:   replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicas }}\n388:   selector:\n389:     matchLabels:\n390:       app: agentcube-router\n391:   template:\n392:     metadata:\n393:       labels:\n394:         app: agentcube-router\n395:     spec:\n396:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n397:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n398:       {{- end }}\n399:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n400:       imagePullSecrets:\n401:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n402:       {{- end }}\n403:       containers:\n404:         - name: agentcube-router\n405:           image: \"{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\"\n406:           imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n407:           ports:\n408:             - name: http\n409:               containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n410:               protocol: TCP\n411:           env:\n412:             - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n413:               valueFrom:\n414:                 fieldRef:\n415:                   fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n416:             - name: REDIS_ADDR\n417:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.addr }}\"\n418:             - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n419:               value: \"{{ .Values.redis.password }}\"\n420:             - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n421:               value: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"\n422:             {{- with .Values.router.extraEnv }}\n423:             {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}\n424:             {{- end }}\n425:           args:\n426:             - --port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n427:             - --debug\n428:           resources:\n429:             {{- toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 12 }}\n430:           livenessProbe:\n431:             httpGet:\n432:               path: /health/live\n433:               port: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n434:             initialDelaySeconds: 1\n435:             periodSeconds: 2\n436:           readinessProbe:\n437:             httpGet:\n438:               path: /health/ready\n439:               port: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n440:             initialDelaySeconds: 1\n441:             periodSeconds: 2\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ### Router Service Template\n445: \n446: ```yaml\n447: apiVersion: v1\n448: kind: Service\n449: metadata:\n450:   name: agentcube-router\n451:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n452:   labels:\n453:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n454: spec:\n455:   type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}\n456:   ports:\n457:     - port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n458:       targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n459:       protocol: TCP\n460:       name: http\n461:   selector:\n462:     app: agentcube-router\n463: ```\n464: \n465: ---\n466: \n467: ## Error Handling\n468: \n469: ### Template Validation Errors\n470: \n471: | Error Type | Cause | Resolution |\n472: |------------|-------|------------|\n473: | `Helm lint error` | Invalid YAML syntax or missing required fields | Fix template syntax, add required fields |\n474: | `Render error` | Undefined template reference or invalid values path | Check helper template names, validate values paths |\n475: | `Missing value` | Required value not provided | Set required values in values.yaml or via `--set` |\n476: | `Invalid resource spec` | Kubernetes API schema violation | Validate against Kubernetes API schema |\n477: \n478: ### Validation Patterns\n479: \n480: ```yaml\n481: {{- if not .Values.redis.addr }}\n482: {{- fail \"redis.addr must be provided\" }}\n483: {{- end }}\n484: \n485: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n486: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n487: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n488: {{- end }}\n489: {{- end }}\n490: ```\n491: \n492: ### Conditional Rendering\n493: \n494: ```yaml\n495: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n496: # RBAC resources rendered\n497: {{- end }}\n498: \n499: {{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}\n500: # Volcano scheduler resources rendered\n501: {{- end }}\n502: \n503: {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n504: imagePullSecrets:\n505:   {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n506: {{- end }}\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## Testing Strategy\n512: \n513: ### Test Categories\n514: \n515: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n516: |----------|-------|-------|\n517: | Helm lint | Chart syntax validation | `helm lint manifests/charts/base` |\n518: | Template render | YAML output validation | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` |\n519: | Values override | Custom values integration | `helm template ... -f custom-values.yaml` |\n520: | E2E deployment | Full stack deployment | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n521: | CRD validation | CRD schema compliance | `kubectl apply --dry-run=client` |\n522: \n523: ### Helm Lint Tests\n524: \n525: ```bash\n526: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n527: # Expected: 0 errors, 0 warnings\n528: ```\n529: \n530: ### Template Render Tests\n531: \n532: ```bash\n533: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n534:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n535:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n536:   > /tmp/rendered.yaml\n537: \n538: # Validate rendered YAML\n539: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml\n540: ```\n541: \n542: ### Values Override Tests\n543: \n544: ```yaml\n545: # test-values.yaml\n546: redis:\n547:   addr: \"redis.test.svc.cluster.local:6379\"\n548:   password: \"test-password\"\n549: router:\n550:   replicas: 2\n551:   rbac:\n552:     create: true\n553:   serviceAccountName: \"test-router-sa\"\n554: workloadmanager:\n555:   replicas: 3\n556:   extraEnv:\n557:     - name: TEST_ENV\n558:       value: \"test-value\"\n559: ```\n560: \n561: ```bash\n562: helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base -f test-values.yaml\n563: ```\n564: \n565: ### E2E Integration Test\n566: \n567: ```bash\n568: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n569:   --namespace agentcube \\\n570:   --create-namespace \\\n571:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n572:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n573:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n574:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n575:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n576:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n577:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n578:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n579:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n580:   --wait\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ### Test Matrix\n584: \n585: | Test Case | Values Override | Expected Output |\n586: |-----------|-----------------|-----------------|\n587: | Default values | None | All components enabled with defaults |\n588: | Router RBAC enabled | `router.rbac.create=true` | Router RBAC resources rendered |\n589: | Volcano scheduler enabled | `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` | Scheduler resources rendered |\n590: | Custom replicas | `router.replicas=3` | Router Deployment spec.replicas=3 |\n591: | Custom resources | `router.resources.limits.cpu=1` | CPU limit overridden |\n592: | Extra environment | `router.extraEnv=[{...}]` | Additional env vars rendered |\n593: | Image override | `router.image.tag=v1.0.0` | Custom image tag used |\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## File Structure\n598: \n599: | Path | Role |\n600: |------|------|\n601: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion) |\n602: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default configuration values |\n603: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template helpers |\n604: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service |\n605: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment + Service |\n606: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | WorkloadManager RBAC (SA, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n607: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Router RBAC (SA, Role, RoleBinding - conditional) |\n608: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Volcano scheduler (conditional) |\n609: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | AgentRuntime CRD |\n610: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | CodeInterpreter CRD |\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## Dependencies\n615: \n616: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n617: |---------|---------|---------|\n618: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template rendering and release management |\n619: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC, CRD |\n620: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD generation from Go types |\n621: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `v0.1.1` | Sandbox CRDs from sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox |\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## Implementation Notes\n626: \n627: ### RBAC Rules\n628: \n629: #### WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n630: \n631: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n632: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n633: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n634: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n635: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n636: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n637: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n638: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n639: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n640: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n641: | `\"\"` (core) | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n642: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n643: | `\"\"` (core) | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n644: \n645: #### Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n646: \n647: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n648: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n649: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n650: \n651: ### Health Probes\n652: \n653: | Component | Liveness Path | Readiness Path | Initial Delay | Period |\n654: |-----------|---------------|----------------|---------------|--------|\n655: | WorkloadManager | `/health` | `/health` | 10s / 5s | 10s / 5s |\n656: | Router | `/health/live` | `/health/ready` | 1s | 2s |\n657: \n658: ### Environment Variables\n659: \n660: | Variable | Source | Component |\n661: |----------|--------|-----------|\n662: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `fieldRef: metadata.namespace` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n663: | `REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n664: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Router, WorkloadManager |\n665: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Constructed from release namespace | Router |\n666: \n667: ### CRD Schema\n668: \n669: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n670: \n671: | Field | Type | Default | Required |\n672: |-------|------|---------|----------|\n673: | `maxSessionDuration` | string | `8h` | Yes |\n674: | `sessionTimeout` | string | `15m` | Yes |\n675: | `podTemplate` | object | - | Yes |\n676: | `targetPort` | array | - | Yes |\n677: \n678: #### CodeInterpreter CRD\n679: \n680: | Field | Type | Default | Required |\n681: |-------|------|---------|----------|\n682: | `authMode` | enum (`picod`, `none`) | `picod` | No |\n683: | `maxSessionDuration` | string | `8h` | No |\n684: | `sessionTimeout` | string | `15m` | No |\n685: | `template` | object | - | Yes |\n686: | `warmPoolSize` | int32 | - | No |\n687: \n688: ---\n689: \n690: ## References\n691: \n692: - Spec: `changes/AR-030/spec.md`\n693: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md`\n694: - Proposal: `changes/AR-030/proposal.md`\n695: - Tasks: `changes/AR-030/tasks.md`\n696: - deployment/design.md — Reference implementation details\n697: - ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage patterns\n698: - project.md — AgentCube project context\n699: - Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values best practices\n700: - Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC schemas\n\n(End of file - total 700 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775884171088,"end":1775884171111}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884171117,"sessionID":"ses_2850e5115ffehvvEY1tK0F0KI3","part":{"id":"prt_d7af1f6f0001EvPzPJNOz7Dfk5","messageID":"msg_d7af1de4e001aUsJ3wNnm0ww6v","sessionID":"ses_2850e5115ffehvvEY1tK0F0KI3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b0494fdebc59482fac39742c016fe8f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Chart Foundation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` with chart metadata\n20:   - Purpose: Define chart name, version, appVersion, and metadata\n21:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`\n22:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\"`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Create `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` with default configuration\n25:   - Purpose: Define default values for all configurable parameters\n26:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n27:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` with named templates\n30:   - Purpose: Define helper templates for name, fullname, labels, selectorLabels, image\n31:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl`\n32:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"app.kubernetes.io/name\"`\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: WorkloadManager Templates (ST-2)\n35: \n36: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `workloadmanager.yaml` Deployment template\n37:   - Purpose: Define WorkloadManager Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources\n38:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n39:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: Deployment\" | head -1`\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment container ports configuration\n42:   - Purpose: Configure container port from `workloadmanager.service.port`\n43:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n44:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set workloadmanager.service.port=9090 | grep \"containerPort: 9090\"`\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment environment variables\n47:   - Purpose: Inject AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE, REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD from values\n48:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n49:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis.test:6379\" --set redis.password=\"secret\" | grep \"REDIS_ADDR\"`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment resources configuration\n52:   - Purpose: Configure CPU/memory limits and requests from `workloadmanager.resources`\n53:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n54:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu=1 | grep \"cpu: 1\"`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.5**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment health probes\n57:   - Purpose: Add livenessProbe and readinessProbe for /health endpoint\n58:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n59:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"livenessProbe\"`\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement WorkloadManager Deployment extraEnv support\n62:   - Purpose: Allow additional environment variables via `workloadmanager.extraEnv`\n63:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n64:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"TEST\",\"value\":\"val\"}]' | grep \"name: TEST\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.7**: Create WorkloadManager Service template\n67:   - Purpose: Define ClusterIP Service for WorkloadManager\n68:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n69:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: Service\"`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.8**: Implement WorkloadManager Service port configuration\n72:   - Purpose: Configure service port from `workloadmanager.service.port`\n73:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n74:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set workloadmanager.service.port=9090 | grep \"port: 9090\"`\n75: \n76: ### Phase 3: Router Templates (ST-3)\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `agentcube-router.yaml` Deployment template\n79:   - Purpose: Define Router Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources\n80:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n81:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"name: agentcube-router\"`\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement Router Deployment container ports configuration\n84:   - Purpose: Configure container port from `router.service.targetPort`\n85:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n86:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.service.targetPort=9090 | grep \"containerPort: 9090\"`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement Router Deployment environment variables\n89:   - Purpose: Inject AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE, REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n90:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n91:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis.test:6379\" --namespace test | grep \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement Router Deployment resources configuration\n94:   - Purpose: Configure CPU/memory limits and requests from `router.resources`\n95:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n96:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.resources.limits.memory=1Gi | grep \"memory: 1Gi\"`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.5**: Implement Router Deployment health probes\n99:   - Purpose: Add livenessProbe (/health/live) and readinessProbe (/health/ready)\n100:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n101:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"path: /health/live\"`\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T3.6**: Implement Router Deployment serviceAccountName support\n104:   - Purpose: Allow custom ServiceAccount via `router.serviceAccountName`\n105:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n106:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"`\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T3.7**: Implement Router Deployment extraEnv support\n109:   - Purpose: Allow additional environment variables via `router.extraEnv`\n110:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n111:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"DEBUG\",\"value\":\"true\"}]' | grep \"name: DEBUG\"`\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T3.8**: Create Router Service template\n114:   - Purpose: Define ClusterIP Service for Router\n115:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n116:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"name: agentcube-router\" | grep \"kind: Service\"`\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T3.9**: Implement Router Service port configuration\n119:   - Purpose: Configure service port and targetPort from values\n120:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n121:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.service.port=80 | grep \"port: 80\"`\n122: \n123: ### Phase 4: RBAC Templates (ST-4)\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T4.1**: Create `templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` ServiceAccount\n126:   - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager (cluster-scoped)\n127:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n128:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\"`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T4.2**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole with full permissions\n131:   - Purpose: Define ClusterRole with permissions for agents.x-k8s.io, runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh, pods, secrets\n132:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n133:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\"`\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T4.3**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n136:   - Purpose: Bind ClusterRole to ServiceAccount\n137:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n138:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRoleBinding\"`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.4**: Create `templates/rbac-router.yaml` with conditional renderin